<subSubSection id="C3411C84A525FF836858B872CB68F9C3" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA525FF826858B872CE09F8BA" blockId="48.[806,1421,1575,1903]" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA525FF826858B872CE77F995" box="[806,1061,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Species with different pleural pattern in males and females. Males with yellow face, posterior anepisternum yellow, anepimeron black, and metafemur mainly black, yellow on basal quarter to third (
<figureCitation id="1360538AA525FF8268EFB8F4C9B0F91E" box="[913,994,1697,1719]" captionStart="Figures 39–50" captionStartId="16.[144,234,1662,1681]" captionTargetBox="[275,1295,194,1618]" captionTargetId="figure-0@16.[271,1295,194,1631]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 39–50. 39–40, Citrogramma solomonense: 39, dorsal view of male abdomen; 40, dorsal view of female abdomen. 41, Citrogramma hervebazini, dorsal view of female abdomen. 42–44, Citrogramma quadricornutum: 42, dorsal view of male abdomen; 43, dorsal view of female abdomen; 44, dorsal view of male scutum and scutellum. 45, Citrogramma fumipenne, dorsal view of male abdomen. 46–49. Citrogramma luteifrons: 46, dorsal view of female head; 47, dorsal view of male abdomen; 48, lateral view of male pleuron and head; 49, dorsal view of female abdomen. 50, Citrogramma schlingeri, dorsal view of male head." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406165/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA525FF826FDBB8F7CF6EF91F" box="[1189,1340,1697,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA525FF826FDBB8F7CF6EF91F" box="[1189,1340,1697,1719]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in coloration of metafemur, abdominal pattern, and by the brownish macula on scutellum (
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA525FF826FC2B88ACF01F95A" box="[1212,1363,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumipenne">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA525FF826FC2B88ACF01F95A" box="[1212,1363,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">C. fumipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has scutellum entirely yellow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA525FF836841B949C951FE1B" blockId="48.[806,1421,1575,1903]" lastBlockId="49.[164,779,198,434]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA525FF8268BAB949CE1DF898" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[964,1103,1820,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA525FF8268BAB949CE1DF898" box="[964,1103,1820,1841]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">C. luteifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, collected from the 
<typeStatus id="54E0F1ADA525FF826E4AB949CFDFF898" box="[1332,1421,1820,1841]" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">neotype</typeStatus>
locality (Heuvelbivak, 
<collectingRegion id="499F81EDA525FF826F56B96ECEE6F8F9" box="[1064,1204,1851,1872]" country="Indonesia" name="Papua Barat" pageId="48" pageNumber="147">West Papua</collectingRegion>
), have anepimeron yellow, slightly darker dorsally on posterior anepimeron, like females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA524FF836AB8BE93C82EFF72" authorityName="MENGUAL" authorityYear="2012" box="[454,636,198,219]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteopleurum">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA524FF836AB8BE93C82EFF72" box="[454,636,198,219]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">C. luteopleurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of both species are very similar, but they can be differentiated by the abdominal pattern, as pointed out in the key. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA524FF836ADBBF77C862FE9E" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[421,560,290,311]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA524FF836ADBBF77C862FE9E" box="[421,560,290,311]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">C. luteifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have some black hairs on notopleuron and they key out with immature females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA524FF836A5EBF0ACB2FFEDD" authorityName="GHORPADE" authorityYear="1994" box="[288,381,351,372]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chola">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA524FF836A5EBF0ACB2FFEDD" box="[288,381,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">C. chola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(couplet 31), but they differ in the coloration of lunule and frons, which is yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA524FF836BDABFC9CB7DFE18" baseAuthorityName="de Meijere" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[164,303,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA524FF836BDABFC9CB7DFE18" box="[164,303,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">C. luteifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
