</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE44F0FA524FF836BC2BDD4C8E5FBE4" blockId="49.[164,779,468,1347]" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">
In the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B348CA524FF836935BDD4CB1DFC1C" authority=", de Meijere (1908)" authorityName=", de Meijere" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteifrons">
<emphasis id="B92F931DA524FF836935BDD4C887FC3C" box="[587,725,896,918]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="148">S. luteifrons</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA32FEA524FF83698EBDD5CB1DFC1C" author="de Meijere JCH" pageId="49" pageNumber="148" pagination="191 - 332" refId="ref55623" refString="de Meijere JCH. 1908. Studien uber sudostasiatische Dipteren. III. Tijdschrift Voor Entomologie 51: 191 - 332. pls. 7 - 8." type="journal article" year="1908">de Meijere (1908)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
wrote that the pleuron was mainly yellow except the ventral portion and a pair of dark brown maculae. These two dark maculae probably correspond to those on anterior section of posterior anepisternum and anepimeron; both areas are dark or black in the material studied from ZMAN.
</paragraph>
